Usage: generateCapTbl [-help] [-cap <float>] [-encrypt] -output <string>
                      [-res <float>] [-xcap <float>] [ -lef <string> [ -shrinkFactor <float> ]] { -ict <string> | -incaptable <string> }

-help                           # Prints out the command usage
-cap <float>                    #   (float, optional)
-encrypt                        # Encrypts the generated capacitance table to
                                # protect the process information in the
                                # capacitance table header. (bool, optional)
-ict <string>                   # To support multiple process corners, a
                                # capacitance table should be created for each
                                # corner from the matching corner ICT file.
                                # (string, optional)
-incaptable <string>            # Specifies the name of an existing capacitance
                                # table in ASCII format. (string, optional)
-lef <string>                   # Specifies the name and the full path to the
                                # process LEF file for optimal accuracy.
                                # (string, optional)
-output <string>                # Specifies the output filename that contains
                                # the capacitance table. (string, required)
-res <float>                    #  Specifies the resistance scaling factor.
                                # (float, optional)
-shrinkFactor <float>           # Specifies the value by which the measurements
                                # in the optional LEF file have to be shrunk
                                # for the technology used with this design.
                                # (float, optional)
-xcap <float>                   # Specifies the cross-coupling capacitance
                                # scaling factor.  (float, optional)